\n\n### Error Handling\n- Validate all inputs before processing\n- Handle AI failures gracefully\n- Provide meaningful error messages\n- Log errors for debugging\n\n### Performance\n- Use appropriate model (gemini-2.5-flash is optimized for speed)\n- Keep prompts concise but complete\n- Cache market data when possible\n- Implement rate limiting in production\n\n## Security\n\n### API Key Management\n- Never hardcode API keys\n- Use environment variables (`GOOGLE_GENAI_API_KEY`)\n- Rotate keys regularly\n- Monitor API usage\n\n### Data Protection\n- Portfolio data is processed in-memory only\n- No persistent storage of user portfolios\n- Market data is anonymized\n- No PII collection\n\n## Testing\n\n### Unit Tests\nCreate tests for:\n- Schema validation\n- Input transformation\n- Output parsing\n- Error cases\n\n### Integration Tests\nTest complete flow:\n- End-to-end analysis\n- Various portfolio types\n- Edge cases (empty portfolio, high concentration)\n- Error scenarios\n\n## Resources\n\n- [Firebase Genkit Documentation](https://firebase.google.com/docs/genkit)\n- [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/)\n- [Gemini API Reference](https://ai.google.dev/docs)\n- [Zod Schema Validation](https://zod.dev/)\n\n## Contributing\n\nWhen adding new AI features:\n1. Create new flows in the `flows/` directory\n2. Follow existing naming conventions\n3. Add comprehensive JSDoc comments\n4. Test thoroughly in Genkit dev UI\n5. Update this README with new flows\n6. Add examples and usage instructions\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n- [ ] Add caching layer for repeated analyses\n- [ ] Implement conversation history for follow-up questions\n- [ ] Add more sophisticated risk models\n- [ ] Support for mutual fund analysis\n- [ ] Integration with real-time market data APIs\n- [ ] Multi-language support\n- [ ] A/B testing for different prompts\n"}"}},{"id":"toolu_01FUrfDbaWEhc6E1oU713cbU","type":"function","function":{"name":"write","arguments":"{"file_path": "src/components/REA