" // Market capitalization\n },\n // ... more stocks\n ]\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { getMockMarketData } from '@/lib/market-data';\n\nconst marketData = await getMockMarketData();\nconst parsed = JSON.parse(marketData);\nconsole.log(parsed.stocks[0].price); // 3927.15\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- Uses `Math.random()` for price fluctuation simulation\n- Fluctuation range: ±5% (0.05 * basePrice)\n- Prices rounded to 2 decimal places\n- Volume simulated between 0-10 million\n- Market cap calculated as basePrice/100 * random multiplier\n\n**Future Enhancements:**\n- Replace with real API integration (NSE/BSE, Alpha Vantage, etc.)\n- Add historical data support\n- Include more metrics (P/E ratio, dividend yield, etc.)\n- Add caching layer\n- Implement WebSocket for live updates\n\n---\n\n### `utils.ts` - General Utilities\n\nCommon utility functions used throughout the application.\n\n#### Functions\n\n**`cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]): string`**\n\nMerges Tailwind CSS class names intelligently, handling conflicts.\n\n**Purpose:**\n- Merge multiple class name strings\n- Handle conditional classes\n- Resolve Tailwind conflicts (e.g., multiple text colors)\n- Remove duplicates\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `clsx` - Construct className strings conditionally\n- `tailwind-merge` - Merge Tailwind classes without conflicts\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { cn } from '@/lib/utils';\n\n// Basic usage\ncn(\"text-base\", \"font-bold\") \n// => \"text-base font-bold\"\n\n// Conditional classes\ncn(\"text-base\", isActive && \"text-blue-500\")\n// => \"text-base text-blue-500\" (if isActive is true)\n\n// Conflict resolution\ncn(\"text-red-500\", \"text-blue-500\")\n// => \"text-blue-500\" (last color wins)\n\n// Array support\ncn([\"text-base\", \"font-bold\"], \"mt-4\")\n// => \"text-base font-bold mt-4\"\n\n// Object support\ncn({ \"text-red-500\": isError, \"text-green-500\": isSuccess })\n// => \"text-red-500\" or \"text-green-500\" based on conditions\n```\n\n**Examples in Components:**\n```typescript\n// Button with conditional styles\n<Button className={cn(\n \"base-button-styles\",\n isLoading && \"opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed\",\n variant === \"primary\" && \"bg-blue-500\",\n variant === \"secondary\" && \"bg-gray-500\"\n)} />\n\n// Card with dynamic borders\n<Card className={cn(\n \"border rounded-lg\",\n hasError && \"border-red-500\",\n isSuccess && \"border-green-500\"\n)} />\n```\n\n---\n\n### `placeholder-images.ts` & `placeholder-images.json`\n\nUtilities for managing placeholder images (if needed for future features).\n\n**Current Usage:** Minimal\n**Future Use Cases:**\n- Stock logo placeholders\n- Company images\n- Chart placeholders during loading\n- Error state images\n\n---\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### Market Data\n1. **Always refresh on analysis** - Get latest data for accurate recommendations\n2. **Error handling** - Handle JSON parsing errors gracefully\n3. **Type safety** - Parse and validate market data structure\n4. **Caching** - Consider caching for production to reduce API calls\n\n### Utilities\n1. **Keep it pure** - Utility functions should be pure (no side effects)\n2. **Type safety** - Add proper TypeScript types\n3. **Documentation** - Add JSDoc comments for complex functions\n4. **Testing** - Write unit tests for all utilities\n\n### File Organization\n```typescript\n// ✅ Good - organized by functionality\nexport const CONSTANT = 'value';\n\nexport function utilityFunction() { ... }\n\nexport type UtilityType = { ... };\n\n// ❌ Bad - mixed concerns\nexport function apiCall() { ... }\nexport function uiHelper() { ... }\n```\n\n## Testing Utilities\n\n### Unit Test Examples\n\n**Testing `cn()` function:**\n```typescript\nimport { cn } from '@/lib/utils';\n\ndescribe('cn utility', () => {\n it('merges class names', () => {\n expect(cn('text-base', 'font-bold')).toBe('text-base font-bold');\n });\n\n it('handles conditionals', () => {\n expect(cn('base', true && 'active')).toBe('base active');\n expect(cn('base', false && 'active')).toBe('base');\n });\n\n it('resolves conflicts', () => {\n expect(cn('text-red-500', 'text-blue-500')).toBe('text-blue-500');\n });\n});\n```\n\n**Testing `getMockMarketData()`:**\n```typescript\nimport { getMockMarketData, MOCK_STOCKS } from '@/lib/market-data';\n\ndescribe('getMockMarketData', () => {\n it('returns valid JSON string', async () => {\n const data = await getMockMarketData();\n expect(() => JSON.parse(data)).not.toThrow();\n });\n\n it('includes all stocks', async () => {\n const data = await getMockMarketData();\n const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n expect(parsed.stocks).toHaveLength(MOCK_STOCKS.length);\n });\n\n it('includes timestamp', async () => {\n const data = await getMockMarketData();\n const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n expect(parsed.generatedAt).toBeDefined();\n });\n\n it('generates different prices on each call', async () => {\n const data1 = await getMockMarketData();\n const data2 = await getMockMarketData();\n expect(data1).not.toBe(data2);\n });\n});\n```\n\n## Adding New Utilities\n\n### When to Add a Utility\n- Function is used in 2+ places\n- Logic is complex and reusable\n- Concerns are separated from components\n- Needs to be testable in isolation\n\n### How to Add\n1. Create function in appropriate file (or new file)\n2. Add TypeScript types\n3. Add JSDoc documentation\n4. Export function\n5. Write unit tests\n6. Update this README\n7. Use in components\n\n### Example Structure\n```typescript\n/**\n * Formats a number as Indian currency (₹).\n * \n * @param amount - The amount to format\n * @param decimals - Number of decimal places (default: 2)\n * @returns Formatted currency string\n * \n * @example\n * formatCurrency(1234.56) // \"₹1,234.56\"\n * formatCurrency(1000, 0) // \"₹1,000\"\n */\nexport function formatCurrency(\n amount: number, \n decimals: number = 2\n): string {\n return `₹${amount.toLocaleString('en-IN', {\n minimumFractionDigits: decimals,\n maximumFractionDigits: decimals,\n })}`;\n}\n```\n\n## Common Utility Patterns\n\n### Number Formatting\n```typescript\n// Currency\nexport const formatCurrency = (amount: number) => \n `₹${amount.toLocaleString('en-IN')}`;\n\n// Percentage\nexport const formatPercent = (value: number) => \n `${value.toFixed(2)}%`;\n\n// Abbreviate large numbers\nexport const abbreviateNumber = (num: number) => {\n if (num >= 1e12) return `${(num / 1e12).toFixed(1)}T`;\n if (num >= 1e9) return `${(num / 1e9).toFixed(1)}B`;\n if (num >= 1e6) return `${(num / 1e6).toFixed(1)}M`;\n if (num >= 1e3) return `${(num / 1e3).toFixed(1)}K`;\n return num.toString();\n};\n```\n\n### Date Formatting\n```typescript\nimport { format } from 'date-fns';\n\nexport const formatDate = (date: Date) => \n format(date, 'MMM dd, yyyy');\n\nexport const formatDateTime = (date: Date) => \n format(date, 'MMM dd, yyyy HH:mm:ss');\n\nexport const getRelativeTime = (date: Date) => {\n const seconds = Math.floor((new Date().getTime() - date.getTime()) / 1000);\n if (seconds < 60) return 'just now';\n if (seconds < 3600) return `${Math.floor(seconds / 60)}m ago`;\n if (seconds < 86400) return `${Math.floor(seconds / 3600)}h ago`;\n return `${Math.floor(seconds / 86400)}d ago`;\n};\n```\n\n### Validation Helpers\n```typescript\nexport const isValidTicker = (ticker: string): boolean => \n /^[A-Z]{1,10}$/.test(ticker);\n\nexport const isValidEmail = (email: string): boolean =>\n /^[^\\s@]+@[^\\s@]+\\.[^\\s@]+$/.test(email);\n\nexport const isPositiveNumber = (value: number): boolean =>\n typeof value === 'number' && value > 0;\n```\n\n### Array Utilities\n```typescript\nexport const groupBy = <T>(\n array: T[], \n key: keyof T\n): Record<string, T[]> => {\n return array.reduce((result, item) => {\n const group = String(item[key]);\n result[group] = result[group] || [];\n result[group].push(item);\n return result;\n }, {} as Record<string, T[]>);\n};\n\nexport const unique = <T>(array: T[]): T[] => \n [...new Set(array)];\n\nexport const s