</div>\n );\n}\n```\n\n#### Implementation Details\n\n- **Breakpoint**: 768px (Tailwind's `md` breakpoint)\n- **Method**: Uses `window.matchMedia` for accurate detection\n- **Updates**: Listens for viewport resize events\n- **SSR Safe**: Returns `undefined` on server, `boolean` on client\n\n#### Return Value\n\n```typescript\nboolean | undefined\n```\n- `true` - Mobile device (width < 768px)\n- `false` - Desktop device (width >= 768px)\n- `undefined` - During server-side rendering\n\n#### Features\n\n- ✅ Real-time viewport tracking\n- ✅ Cleanup on unmount\n- ✅ Performance optimized (uses native API)\n- ✅ TypeScript support\n\n#### Example Use Cases\n\n**Conditional Rendering:**\n```typescript\nconst isMobile = useMobile();\n\nreturn isMobile ? (\n <MobileMenu />\n) : (\n <DesktopSidebar />\n);\n```\n\n**Conditional Styling:**\n```typescript\nconst isMobile = useMobile();\n\nreturn (\n <div className={cn(\n \"container\",\n isMobile ? \"p-2\" : \"p-8\"\n )}>\n Content\n </div>\n);\n```\n\n**Dynamic Props:**\n```typescript\nconst isMobile = useMobile();\n\nreturn (\n <Table \n columns={isMobile ? mobileColumns : desktopColumns}\n pageSize={isMobile ? 5 : 10}\n />\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### `use-toast.ts` - Toast Notifications\n\nManages toast notifications for user feedback.\n\n#### Usage\n\n```typescript\nimport { useToast } from '@/hooks/use-toast';\n\nfunction MyComponent() {\n const { toast } = useToast();\n \n const handleSuccess = () => {\n toast({\n title: \"Success!\",\n description: \"Your portfolio has been analyzed.\",\n });\n };\n \n const handleError = () => {\n toast({\n title: \"Error\",\n description: \"Failed to analyze portfolio.\",\n variant: \"destructive\",\n });\n };\n \n return (\n <>\n <Button onClick={handleSuccess}>Success</Button>\n <Button onClick={handleError}>Error</Button>\n </>\n );\n}\n```\n\n#### Toast Options\n\n```typescript\ntype ToastProps = {\n title?: string; // Toast title\n description?: string; // Toast description/message\n variant?: \"default\" | \"destructive\"; // Visual style\n duration?: number; // Duration in ms (default: 5000)\n action?: ToastActionElement; // Action button\n};\n```\n\n#### Variants\n\n**Default Toast:**\n```typescript\ntoast({\n title: \"Information\",\n description: \"Portfolio updated successfully.\",\n});\n```\n\n**Destructive/Error Toast:**\n```typescript\ntoast({\n title: \"Error\",\n description: \"Something went wrong.\",\n variant: \"destructive\",\n});\n```\n\n**Toast with Action:**\n```typescript\ntoast({\n title: \"Portfolio saved\",\n description: \"Your changes have been saved.\",\n action: (\n <ToastAction altText=\"Undo\">Undo</ToastAction>\n ),\n});\n```\n\n**Custom Duration:**\n```typescript\ntoast({\n title: \"Quick message\",\n description: \"This will disappear in 2 seconds.\",\n duration: 2000,\n});\n```\n\n#### API Methods\n\n**`toast(props: ToastProps): void`**\n- Creates and displays a new toast notification\n- Automatically dismisses after duration\n- Queues if multiple toasts are shown\n\n**`dismiss(toastId?: string): void`**\n- Dismisses a specific toast by ID\n- Dismisses all toasts if no ID provided\n\n```typescript\nconst { toast, dismiss } = useToast();\n\n// Show toast\nconst toastId = toast({ title: \"Loading...\" });\n\n// Dismiss specific toast\ndismiss(toastId);\n\n// Dismiss all toasts\ndismiss();\n```\n\n#### Integration\n\n**Add Toaster Component:**\n```typescript\n// In app/layout.tsx\nimport { Toaster } from '@/components/ui/toaster';\n\nexport default function RootLayout({ children }) {\n return (\n <html>\n <body>\n {children}\n <Toaster />\n </body>\n </html>\n );\n}\n```\n\n#### Example Use Cases\n\n**Success Notification:**\n```typescript\nconst handleAnalyze = async () => {\n try {\n const result = await analyzePortfolio(data);\n toast({\n title: \"Analysis Complete\",\n description: `Analyzed ${result.advice.length} stocks.`,\n });\n } catch (error) {\n // Error handling...\n }\n};\n```\n\n**Error Handling:**\n```type