>\n) {\n const { portfolio, marketData, cash } = analyzeActionSchema.parse(input);\n\n const analysisInput = {\n portfolio: portfolio,\n marketData: marketData,\n cash: cash,\n };\n\n const result = await analyzePortfolio(analysisInput);\n \n return result;\n}\n```\n\n**Features:**\n- ✅ Type-safe with Zod validation\n- ✅ Server-side execution (`'use server'`)\n- ✅ Input sanitization and validation\n- ✅ Error handling\n- ✅ Calls AI flow for analysis\n\n**Input Schema:**\n```typescript\n{\n portfolio: Array<{\n ticker: string;\n shares: number;\n }>;\n marketData: string; // JSON string\n cash: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Output:**\nReturns `AnalyzePortfolioOutput` from AI flow:\n```typescript\n{\n advice: Array<{\n ticker: string;\n recommendation: 'buy' | 'sell' | 'hold' | 'diversify';\n reason: string;\n riskLevel: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';\n amount?: number;\n percentage?: number;\n }>;\n generatedAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Usage in Components:**\n```typescript\nimport { getAnalysisAction } from '@/app/actions/analyze';\n\nconst result = await getAnalysisAction({\n portfolio: [\n { ticker: 'TCS', shares: 10 },\n { ticker: 'RELIANCE', shares: 5 }\n ],\n marketData: JSON.stringify(marketData),\n cash: 50000\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## ️ Routing\n\n### Current Routes\n\n| Path | Component | Description |\n|------|-----------|-------------|\n| `/` | `page.tsx` | Home page with portfolio analyzer |\n\n### Future Routes\n\n```\napp/\n├── page.tsx # Home\n├── dashboard/\n│ └── page.tsx # Dashboard (future)\n├── history/\n│ └── page.tsx # Analysis history (future)\n├── settings/\n│ └── page.tsx # User settings (future)\n└── api/\n └── webhook/\n └── route.ts # API webhook (future)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Styling Strategy\n\n### Tailwind CSS\n- **Utility-first** approach\n- **Custom theme** in `tailwind.config.ts`\n- **Responsive design** with breakpoints\n- **Dark mode** support (configured)\n\n### CSS Variables\n- Defined in `globals.css`\n- Used for theming\n- Easily customizable\n- Support for light/dark modes\n\n### Component Styles\n- Inline Tailwind classes\n- `cn()` utility for conditional classes\n- No CSS modules (using Tailwind)\n\n---\n\n## Server Actions Best Practices\n\n### 1. Always Validate Input\n```typescript\n// ✅ Good - Zod validation\nconst schema = z.object({ ... });\nconst validated = schema.parse(input);\n\n// ❌ Bad - No validation\nasync function action(input: any) {\n // Directly using input\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Use 'use server' Directive\n```typescript\n'use server';\n\nexport async function myAction() {\n // This runs on the server only\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Error Handling\n```typescript\nexport async function action(input: Input) {\n try {\n const result = await someOperation(input);\n return { success: true, data: result };\n } catch (error) {\n return { \n success: false, \n error: error.message \n };\n }\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Type Safety\n```typescript\n// Define types for inputs and outputs\ntype ActionInput = z.infer<typeof schema>;\ntype ActionOutput = {\n success: boolean;\n data?: ResultType;\n error?: string;\n};\n\nexport async function action(\n input: ActionInput\n): Promise<ActionOutput> {\n // Implementation\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Metadata & SEO\n\n### Static Metadata\n```typescript\nexport const metadata: Metadata = {\n title: 'MarketSage',\n description: 'AI-powered stock portfolio analysis',\n keywords: ['stocks', 'portfolio', 'AI', 'India'],\n authors: [{ name: 'Your Name' }],\n openGraph: {\n title: 'MarketSage',\n description: 'AI-powered stock analysis',\n type: 'website',\n },\n};\n```\n\n### Dynamic Metadata\nFor future dynamic pages:\n```typescript\nexport async function generateMetadata(\n { params }: { params: { id: string } }\n): Promise<Metadata> {\n const data = await fetchData(params.id);\n \n return {\n title: data.title,\n description: data.description,\n };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Performance Optimizations\n\n### Server Components (Default)\n- Reduces JavaScript bundle size\n- Faster initial page load\n- Better SEO\n\n### Client Components (When Needed)\nUse `'use client'` only when:\n- Using React hooks (useState, useEffect)\n- Handling browser events\n- Using browser APIs\n- Need interactivity\n\n### Code Splitting\nNext.js automatically code-splits by route.\n\n### Image Optimization\n```typescript\nimport Image from 'next/image';\n\n<Image \n src=\"/logo.png\" \n alt=\"Logo\" \n width={100} \n height={100}\n priority // For above-fold images\n/>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n### Testing Pages\n```typescript\nimport { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';\nimport Home from '@/app/page';\n\ndescribe('Home Page', () => {\n it('renders the main component', () => {\n render(<Home />);\n expect(screen.getByRole('main')).toBeInTheDocument();\n });\n});\n```\n\n### Testing Server Actions\n```typescript\nimport { getAnalysisAction } from '@/app/actions/analyze';\n\ndescribe('getAnalysisAction', () => {\n it('returns analysis results', async () => {\n const result = await getAnalysisAction({\n portfolio: [{ ticker: 'TCS', shares: 10 }],\n marketData: '{}',\n cash: 50000,\n });\n \n expect(result.advice).toBeDefined();\n });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## Adding New Pages\n\n### Step 1: Create Page File\n```typescript\n// app/new-page/page.tsx\nexport default function NewPage() {\n return <div>New Page Content</div>;\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2: Add Metadata\n```typescript\nimport type { Metadata } from 'next';\n\nexport const metadata: Metadata = {\n title: 'New Page - MarketSage',\n description: 'Description of the new page',\n};\n```\n\n### Step 3: Add Navigation\nUpdate header or navigation component.\n\n### Step 4: Add Server Actions (if needed)\n```typescript\n// app/actions/new-action.ts\n'use server';\n\nexport async function newAction() {\n // Server logic\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Loading & Error States\n\n### Loading UI\n```typescript\n// app/loading.tsx\nexport default function Loading() {\n return <div>Loading...</div>;\n}\n```\n\n### Error UI\n```typescript\n// app/error.tsx\n'use client';\n\nexport default function Error({\n error,\n reset,\n}: {\n error: Error;\n reset: () => void;\n}) {\n return (\n <div>\n <h2>Something went wrong!</h2>\n <button onClick={() => reset()}>Try again</button>\n </div>\n );\n}\n```\n\n### Not Found\n```typescript\n// app/not-found.tsx\nexport default function NotFound() {\n return <div>404 - Page Not Found</div>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Resources\n\n- [Next.js App Router Documentation](https://nextjs.org/docs/app)\n- [Server Actions](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/data-fetching/server-actions-and-mutations)\n- [Metadata](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/optimizing/metadata)\n- [Routing](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/routing)\n\n---\n\n## Contributing\n\nWhen adding new routes:\n1. Follow the file-based routing convention\n2. Add proper metadata for SEO\n3. Use server components by default\n4. Add loading and error states\n5. Validate all server action inputs\n6. Update this README with new routes\n7. Add tests for new functionality\n"}"}}]},{"role":"tool","name":"write","tool_call_id":"toolu_01KMZccUCKJD6Sz3X44BHKsZ","content":"Wrote contents to C:/Users/HP/IdeaProjects/MarketSage/src/app/README.md.

