y\n- **Revoke immediately** if compromised\n\n#### Environment Variables\n```bash\n# ✅ DO: Use .env.local for sensitive data\nGOOGLE_GENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here\n\n# ❌ DON'T: Hardcode in source files\nconst apiKey = \"hardcoded_key\"; // NEVER DO THIS\n```\n\n#### Data Privacy\n- **No sensitive data** in portfolio names or notes\n- **Clear browser cache** after use on shared computers\n- **Use HTTPS** in production environments\n- **Review permissions** before granting access\n\n### For Developers\n\n#### Code Security\n\n**1. Input Validation**\n```typescript\n// ✅ Always validate user input\nconst schema = z.object({\n ticker: z.string().max(10),\n shares: z.number().positive(),\n});\nconst validated = schema.parse(input);\n\n// ❌ Never trust raw input\nconst value = req.body.value; // Unsafe\n```\n\n**2. Server Actions**\n```typescript\n// ✅ Use 'use server' directive\n'use server';\n\nexport async function serverAction(input: Input) {\n // Validate input\n // Process securely\n}\n\n// ❌ Don't expose sensitive operations to client\nexport function dangerousAction() {\n // Exposed to client\n}\n```\n\n**3. Environment Variables**\n```typescript\n// ✅ Server-side only\nconst apiKey = process.env.GOOGLE_GENAI_API_KEY;\n\n// ❌ Never expose to client\nconst NEXT_PUBLIC_API_KEY = process.env.API_KEY; // BAD!\n```\n\n**4. Dependencies**\n```bash\n# ✅ Regularly update dependencies\nnpm audit\nnpm audit fix\n\n# ✅ Check for vulnerabilities\nnpm install -g snyk\nsnyk test\n```\n\n**5. XSS Prevention**\n```typescript\n// ✅ React escapes by default\n<div>{userInput}</div> // Safe\n\n// ⚠️ Dangerous - avoid if possible\n<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: userInput }} /> // Unsafe\n\n// ✅ Sanitize if HTML is necessary\nimport DOMPurify from 'dompurify';\n<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: DOMPurify.sanitize(userInput) }} />\n```\n\n**6. CSRF Protection**\n- Next.js Server Actions have built-in CSRF protection\n- Use proper HTTP methods (GET for reads, POST for writes)\n- Validate origin headers in production\n\n**7. SQL Injection Prevention**\n```typescript\n// ✅ Use parameterized queries (when DB is added)\nconst result = await db.query(\n 'SELECT * FROM portfolios WHERE user_id = $1',\n [userId]\n);\n\n// ❌ Never concatenate user input\nconst result = await db.query(\n `SELECT * FROM portfolios WHERE user_id = ${userId}` // BAD!\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n## Authentication & Authorization\n\n### Current State\n- No authentication implemented yet\n- All data is client-side only\n- No user accounts or data persistence\n\n### Future Implementation (Planned)\n- NextAuth.js for authentication\n- Role-based access control\n- Secure session management\n- OAuth providers (Google, GitHub)\n- Two-factor authentication (2FA)\n\n---\n\n## API Security\n\n### Google AI API\n\n**Key Management:**\n```bash\n# ✅ Development\nGOOGLE_GENAI_API_KEY=dev_key_here\n\n# ✅ Production\n# Use Firebase App Hosting secrets\n# Or environment variables in deployment platform\n```\n\n**Rate Limiting:**\n- Implement rate limiting to prevent abuse\n- Monitor API usage patterns\n- Set up alerts for unusual activity\n\n**Error Handling:**\n```typescript\n// ✅ Don't expose sensitive error details\ncatch (error) {\n console.error('API Error:', error); // Log internally\n return { error: 'An error occurred' }; // Generic message to user\n}\n\n// ❌ Don't expose stack traces\ncatch (error) {\n return { error: error.stack }; // Exposes internals\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Network Security\n\n### HTTPS\n- **Always use HTTPS** in production\n- **Redirect HTTP to HTTPS**\n- **Use HSTS headers**\n- **Secure cookies** (SameSite, Secure flags)\n\n### CORS\n```typescript\n// next.config.ts\nconst nextConfig = {\n async headers() {\n return [\n {\n source: '/api/:path*',\n headers: [\n { key: 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin', value: 'https://yourdomain.com' },\n { key: 'Access-Control-Allow-Methods', value: 'POST, OPTIONS' },\n ],\n },\n ];\n },\n};\n```\n\n### Content Security Policy\n```t